numer — TODO
============

Done
----

[x] Multi-line text editor (nano-style navigation)
[x] Live expression evaluation per line
[x] Result column on the right
[x] Centered layout with horizontal padding
[x] Striped odd-line background
[x] Arithmetic operators: + - * / % ^
[x] Operator precedence and grouping with parentheses
[x] Right-associative power (2^3^2 = 512)
[x] Unary minus / plus
[x] Built-in math functions: sqrt, abs, floor, ceil, round,
    sin, cos, tan, asin, acos, atan, atan2, log, ln, log2,
    log10, exp, pow, max, min, sum
[x] Built-in constants: pi, e, tau, phi
[x] User-defined variables (case-insensitive)
[x] `last` variable (result of previous line)
[x] Comments with # and //
[x] Error indicator (✗) for invalid expressions
[x] Undo / Redo (Ctrl+Z / Ctrl+Y, up to 100 snapshots)
[x] File persistence — open and save .nm files
[x] Save-as prompt for untitled sessions (Ctrl+S)
[x] Safe path handling (~ expansion, null bytes, parent dir check)
[x] Dirty indicator in status bar
[x] Syntax highlighting: numbers, operators, functions,
    constants, variables, parentheses, comments
[x] Horizontal scroll for long lines
[x] Home / End / PgUp / PgDn navigation
[x] Ctrl+K kill to end of line
[x] go install support (module path github.com/gfonseca/numer)
[x] Example sheet: home expenses budget

Ideas
-----

[ ] Multiple cursors / column selection
[ ] Hex / binary / octal number literals (0xff, 0b1010)
[ ] Unit conversions (km to miles, kg to lb, etc.)
[ ] Sum of a range of lines
[ ] Export results to plain text or CSV
[ ] Search / jump to line
[ ] Configurable result column width
[ ] Configurable color theme
[ ] Mouse support (click to position cursor)
[ ] Open recent files
